Great app, would love to see support for 7z built in file hashing options, 
i saw app already had md5 under file info which isn't included in 7z by 
default and that's awesome (never understood why it wasn't included by 
default) and i would kill for tar-.par2 creation but would probably be to 
much work on the dev to add as its not natively supported in 7z, But it 
sure would give this app a stand out feature that other apps dont offer 
(parity archive's) and maybe put rar recovery record's to shame. currently 
the only option we even have thats close is old tar.bz2 (at least some 
recovery options), but adding custom archiving functions adds tons of 
complexity and slows down future updates, so i have no complaints its great 
as it is and am looking forwards to what future updates bring.

An all around solid app with great performance, ZArchiver is a vital component of Android for any power user. It can open and extract files from just about any archive, including RARs. It can also compress multiple files and folders into a single archive: ZIP (compatibility), 7z (best compression), and several other formats. You can encrypt files, test integrity, and even split/open multi-volume archives. I recently bought ZArchiver Pro to support the dev, and I'm very happy with it! :)
